  "text": "Additionally, [CITATION_1] highlight that, even if an environment is not truly random, the agent can get stuck in some parts of the environment. To illustrate this, the authors placed a television in their 3D environment and added a specific action to randomly change the picture of the displayed picture. It turns out that their agent (ICM and prediction with random features) kept looking at the picture. It would be interesting to test a broader class of algorithms in order to test their abilities to handle such a difficult stochastic setting.",
